-- 
National Bank Offers to Buy Smaller Rival Alpha Bank

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 
2011-02-18T14:17:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/national-bank-of-greece-bids-for-alpha-bank-nation-s-third-largest-lender.html
(Corrects in second paragraph to show 8 new National Bank
shares for 11 existing Alpha shares.)    National Bank of Greece SA , the
country’s largest lender, offered to buy Alpha Bank SA, Greece’s
third biggest bank.  National will offer 8 new National Bank shares for 11
existing Alpha shares, a share ratio of 0.727 National shares
for each Alpha share, according to an e-mailed statement from
National Bank today.  The offer aims to create the strongest bank in Greece and
one of the biggest in southeast  Europe , the statement said.
Shares in the two banks were earlier suspended from trading on
the Athens bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Petrakis in Athens at 
